(720, 'The Camera Never Lies', 'Film, images & historical interpretation in the 20th century for those who have a general interest in photojournalism, and films based on historical events.', 'This short course is an introduction to use of images and other media as historical\nevidence in the twentieth century, issues of authenticity and manipulation,\nand the place of film and historical adoptions as public history.&nbsp;', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/lyingcamera', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g_jMGNos7wQ', '2013-06-24', 6, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/46/fb5637e5b6d4e71b0b97cfeb0aec55/Flag-raising-on-Iwo-Jima.jpg', 'Humanities ', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', ' University of London', '2014-05-18 22:41:19'),
