(886, 'Recovering the Humankind Past and Saving the Universal Heritage', 'Archaeology has as its objective the recovery and revival of humankind past, and as its aim the rescue and preservation of cultural heritage.', 'Archaeology has\n        as its objective the recovery and revival of humankind past,\n        and as its aim\n        the rescue and preservation of cultural heritage. The past was\n        always the\n        object of attention in the ancient civilizations. In the modern\n        world,\n        Archaeology is no longer about the&nbsp;classification of found objects, but rather about&nbsp;understanding ancient\n        cultures. Its fascination is precisely in its methods: a path\n        inevitably\n        fluctuating between identity and alterity. <br>', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/recoveringthepast', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=', '3000-00-00', 6, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/37/58140776ad96610f665a55ba21a7ba/Matthiae_Ebla.jpg', 'Humanities ', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', ' Sapienza University of Rome', '2014-05-18 22:42:03'),
(887, 'Terrorism and Counterterrorism: Comparing Theory and Practice', 'Students, policy makers, journalists or anyone with a strong interest in terrorism and counter terrorism studies and trends will find the course most relevant. It will equip you with a range of insights that help you to analyze and understand these complex phenomena. ', '<p>\n\n</p>\n<p>Terrorism has arguably been one of the defining factors of our age. It frequently makes headlines, threatening or attacking governments, private business and ordinary citizens. And in many parts of the world, it has been one of the most important threats\n    to peace, security and stability. But what does this exactly mean? What is the nature of this threat? Who or what is threatened, how, by whom and why? What can be done about it or how can we at least limit the impact of terrorism and make sure that\n    terrorists do not make headlines and manage to scare us?</p>\n<p>These are just a handful of questions that will be addressd in this course that consists of three parts. First it focuses on the essence of terrorism as an instrument to achieve certain goals, in addition to an exploration of this phenomenon and the\n    difficulties in defining it. The second part provides an overview of the state of the art in (counter) terrorism studies. Since ‘9/11’ terrorism studies have grown exponentially, reflecting the rise in perceived threats. But what has academia come\n    up with? What theories, assumptions and conventional wisdom has it produced that could be of help in understanding terrorism and dealing with it? The most interesting results are examined and compared with empirical evidence with the aim to either\n    stress their importance or to debunk them as myths. The final part looks into the implications and possibilities for policy making.</p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/terrorism', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hQFzxDSpvNM', '2013-09-30', 5, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/29/5d4f6dfbd7b529d18d0c834ace525e/Terrorism-and-Counterterrorism.jpg', 'Humanities ', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', ' Universiteit Leiden', '2014-05-18 22:42:03'),
