(1382, 'Developing Data Products', 'Learn the basics of creating data products using Shiny, R packages, and interactive graphics. This is the ninth course in the Johns Hopkins Data Science Specialization.', 'A data product is the production output from a statistical analysis. Data products automate complex analysis tasks or use technology to expand the utility of a data informed model, algorithm or inference. This course covers the basics of creating data products using Shiny, R packages, and interactive graphics. The course will focus on the statistical fundamentals of creating a data product that can be used to tell a story about data to a mass audience.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/devdataprod', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qPqeLBxPsNo', '3000-00-00', 4, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/b6/fd088169b511e39de639278c4f9dba/DevelopingDataProducts.jpg', 'Information, Tech & Design', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', ' Johns Hopkins University', '2014-05-18 22:44:18'),
